ss=title> History about Lesvos Island</span><hr size=1> History of Lesvos Island<br>
Years and years ago, there was a great Amazon Queen, named Myrine. Her skills were learned by Ares himself, who was infact, her father.<br>
<br>
She claimed a large Island in the Agean Sea and it was named after her. Her travells did not end there. Her tribe and her travelled to another island, naming it Lesvos. Clearing an area of the forest, she built a great fortress, to protect her Amazons from dangers. <br>
<br>
One night, she and Ares concieved the next in line, Kyme.<br>
<br>
Kyme took the position of Queen when her mothers time had passed and she left for the Amazon Lands of the Dead.<br>
<br>
Around the same time that Kyme took hold of Lesvos, the southern most part of the island was inhabited by a large group of Cannibles. The cannibles and amazons were always feuding. <br>
<br>
During these feuds, Ares pregnated Kyme, and Velaska was born. <br>
<br>
When Velaska was twelve years old, a great war with the cannibles broke out, many amazons died, including her mother, Kyme. <br>
As luck would have it, Velaska was able to steal her body back from the cannibles before the unthinkable was done.<br>
<br>
Seeing as by Lesvosian Law, to be the Queen, the heir to the throne must have gotten her cycle and must have had it for 12 New Moons. Velaska had not had her cycle yet, so the title went to her mothers Second in Command, Melousa, who tried to break the Lesvosian Amazons out of there blood thirsty ways.<br>
<br>
Not approving these new ways, Velaska left and went to Themiscrya, by invitation of her friend De'Lerium. Once there, she tranied furiously up until the day she recieved her cycle.<br>
<br>
12 New Moons later, she returned to Lesvos. At this time Melousa refused to give up the title of Queen. Velaska defeated her in a battle for the crown.<br>
<br>
Velaska waged a full scale war against the Cannibles, with Ares help, they defeated the enemy.<br>
<br>
This is how Lesvos came to being.  <p>Queen Velaska of Lesvos Island<br>
High Priestess of Hera.. <br>
Warrior for the Amazon Nation.. <br>
Year round Bad ass..<br>
<br>
